Makefile.am: clean up

Convenience libraries are implicitly static and do not need
-no-undefined or linker flags. Also use the full -version-info.
test-build.sh: Skip the sanitizer tests on musl

build: Workaround for -Ofast

Workaround for issue https://github.com/orbea/trio/issues/1.

Also strio.h is only used by example.c.

Fix test-build.sh for clang15

With clang15 the following warning is emitted when linking:

  clang-15: error: '-x c++' after last input file has no effect [-Werror,-Wunused-command-line-argument]

The problem is that automake adds the CFLAGS variable to both the
COMPILE and LINK variables. However -xc++ should be only used in the
COMPILE variable and clang15 now warns about this. The solution is to
set it in the CPPFLAGS variable instead which is only added to COMPILE.

Fix make check failure with -Ofast

With -Ofast which enables -funsafe-math-optimizations the value of
integerNumber becomes 0.0 instead of 1.0 which breaks the logic and
regression test program. Adding espilonCorrection which is also 0.0
prevents the compiler from optimizing the value away.

This is part of issue https://github.com/orbea/trio/issues/1.

Clean up whitespace

Remove trailing whitespace:

find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -iname '*\.c' | xargs sed -i 's/[ \t]*$//
find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -iname '*\.h' | xargs sed -i 's/[ \t]*$//

Squash extra blank lines:

find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -iname '*\.c' -o -name '*\.h' | while read -r i; do
  cat -s "$i" > "$i.new"
  mv "$i.new" "$i"
done

Remove register keyword.

Fixes -xc++ -std=c++17 warning.
